                If you do not agree to these Terms, you are free to reject them; unfortunately, that means you will not be able to use the Services. If you use the Services in any way, that means you agree to all of these Terms, and these Terms will remain in effect while you use the Services. These Terms include the provisions in this document, as well as those in the Privacy Policy.
              </p>

              <hr />

              <!-- 2. The Services -->
              <h2 id="the-services">The Services</h2>
              <p>
                As a condition to using the Services, you are required to open an account with Handoff and select a password and username, and to provide certain other information about yourself as prompted by the registration form. You represent and warrant that: (a) all required registration information you submit is truthful and accurate; (b) you will maintain the accuracy of such information. You may delete your account at any time, for any reason, by following the instructions on the Site. Handoff may suspend or terminate your account in accordance with the Terms.
              </p>
              <p>The Services provided by Handoff include, but are not limited to:</p>
              <ul>
                <li><strong>Universal Catalog API:</strong> This service provides direct API access to material prices. Users can integrate this API into their own systems to retrieve up-to-date pricing information for various construction materials.</li>
                <li><strong>Handoff:</strong> This service allows users, who are general contractors, to generate estimates for their customers and electronically sign these estimates. The Handoff service streamlines the estimating process and facilitates secure, electronic agreement between contractors and their clients.</li>
                <li><strong>Voice-to-Text Feature:</strong> This service allows users to create project descriptions and estimates using voice input, which is then transcribed into text.</li>
              </ul>
              <p>
                You may not (i) select or use as a username or other identifier with the intent to impersonate another person; (ii) use as a username or other identifier a name subject to any rights of a person other than you without appropriate authorization; or (iii) use as a username or other identifier a name that is otherwise offensive, vulgar, or obscene.
              </p>
              <p>
